Privacy Policy for Chip
Last Updated: April 1, 2026

This Privacy Policy explains how Chip ("the Bot") collects, uses, and protects your data when you use it within Discord. By adding the Bot to your server or interacting with it, you consent to the practices described in this policy.

1. Data We Collect
To provide its features and function properly on Discord, the Bot may collect and store the following information:

Command Usage: We may log when commands are executed and by whom to monitor bot performance and prevent abuse.

2. How We Use Your Data
The data we collect is used strictly for the operation and improvement of the Bot. Specifically, we use your data to:

Execute commands and provide the Bot's core functionality.

Identify and troubleshoot bugs or technical issues.

Prevent abuse, spam, and violations of our Terms of Service.

3. Data Storage and Security
We do not store anything.

4. Data Sharing and Disclosure
We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal data to third parties. We will only share your data in the following circumstances:

To comply with the law: If legally required to do so by a valid subpoena, court order, or law enforcement request.

To enforce rules: To enforce our Terms of Service or investigate potential violations.

With Discord: Data is inherently shared with Discord as part of the Bot's operation, and your use of the Bot is also governed by Discord’s Privacy Policy.

5. Data Retention and Deletion
We do not retain any of your data, this is governed by Discord’s Privacy Policy.

6. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make significant changes, we will notify users via our support server or through a bot announcement. Continued use of the Bot after changes are published constitutes your acceptance of the new policy.